name: Algorithms and Data Structures (Arrays, Matrices, Trees ...)
description:
A drawing library for all things related to Algorithms and Data Structures (including Trees).
It includes drawing useful for :
- Arrays (numbered and not numbered, length 10 or 20)
- Datasets & Hashing table ( numbered, size 5)
- Datatables (vertical, size 5)
- Linked lists (vertical and horizontal, size 5)
- Trees (height 1, 2, 3 and 4) (Binary : Heap, Red-black, AVL, Splay)
- Red-black tree items ( single black NIL, double black NIL, right and left rotation arrows, black filter and red filter)
- Matrices (numbered, 3x3, 4x4, 5x5, 10x10)

All numbered structures start by 0 ;)

name: AWS Architecture Icons
description: This library is a collection of the most popular AWS Architecture Icons to help you build diagrams using Excalidraw. Storage services and databases: S3, EBS, EFS, RDS, Aurora, DynamoDB. Compute: EC2, Lambda, Fargate. Analytics: Kinesis, Glue Crawler, Glue DataCatalog, Athena. Application integration: SNS, SQS, AppSync, Step Functions, EventBridge, API Gateway. Developer tools: CodeCommit, CodeBuilt, CodeDeploy. Management: CloudWatch, CloudFormation, Systems Manager. Networking: VPN gateway, Peering connection, NAT gateway, Internet gateway, NACL, Transit gateway, CloudFront, ELB. Other: Cognito, SES, Amplify, AWS Account, AWS Region, IAM, Chatbot, Sagemaker Train, Sagemaker Model, Sagemaker Canvas, Sagemaker Notebook, Amazon Elastic Inference, Sagemaker Ground Truth, Sagemaker, Kinesis Data Firehose, Kinesis Video Streams, Kinesis Data Streams, Kinesis Data Analytics, QuickSight, EMR, Data Pipeline, Redshift, Lake Formation, Glue.
